<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 4:42PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern Osage,
northern Washington and northwestern Nowata Counties through 515 PM
CDT...
At 441 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms near
Grainola, 4 miles southwest of Elgin, 2 miles northwest of Hulah and
4 miles northwest of Wann. These storms were nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Copan...                          Wann...
Elgin...                          Grainola...
Hulah...                          Wah Sha She State Park...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
